The paper deals with the problem of resource selection in distributed systems, which is a core topic in the field of Distributed Computing (cs.DC). The authors also mention the use of matchmaking algorithms, which are commonly used in Networked and Distributed Systems (cs.NI). The paper also involves the development of a model to estimate the cost of running tasks on different resources, which is related to Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the use of the model for workload optimization, which is a topic in Systems and Control (cs.SY).
